    <h3><span style="border: 1px solid black">Discovering My University - KNU</span></h3>
    <a href="https://help-rectorat.knu.ua/abit">Explore the University</a>
    <blockquote style="border:2px solid #c87184">
        Established in 1834, Taras Shevchenko National University of Kyiv (KNU) stands tall as Ukraine’s premier national higher
        education institution. Throughout its illustrious history, the university has seamlessly blended high-quality education with cutting-edge science, honoring tradition while embracing innovation. KNU boasts a rich legacy of accomplishments, serving as the preferred choice for talented students who, in return, gain the opportunity to emerge as leaders in their respective fields, professions, and public life.

        Presently, Shevchenko University comprises 13 faculties, 7 educational and scientific institutes, 3 educational institutes, 1 educational and scientific center, 2 colleges, 1 lyceum, and preparatory departments. More than 25,000 students, including around 2,000 international students, and approximately 2,000 educators actively participate in over 600 training and scientific programs spanning 25 fields and 59 disciplines.
    </blockquote>
    

